---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  lang="en"
  title="Privacy Policy — loam.dev"
  description="Privacy policy for loam.dev: self-hosted fonts, no cookies, no tracking. Data flows: Cloudflare access logs and a GitHub API call on the home page only."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <div class="prose-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <section>
      <h2>Controller</h2>
      <p>
        Silvio Lindstedt<br>
        <a href="mailto:silvio-lindstedt@outlook.com">silvio-lindstedt@outlook.com</a>
      </p>
      <p>No postal address is required here — this is a non-commercial open-source project to which §5 DDG does not apply.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Hosting &amp; Infrastructure</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted on <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong> (Cloudflare, Inc., 101 Townsend St., San Francisco, CA 94107, USA).
        Cloudflare automatically records standard server access logs (IP address, browser, page requested, timestamp) for every request.
        These logs are processed by Cloudflare in its role as a data processor and are subject to
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.
        The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR — legitimate interest in operating a secure, functional website.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cloudflare may transfer data to the United States. Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) are in place.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Fonts</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses <strong>Spline Sans Mono</strong>, served <strong>self-hosted</strong> from this domain via
        <code>@fontsource/spline-sans-mono</code>.
        No request is made to the Google Fonts CDN or any other third-party font service.
        Your IP address is never sent to Google for font loading.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>GitHub API Call (Home Page Only)</h2>
      <p>
        The home page makes a <strong>direct client-side fetch</strong> to the public
        <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/rest" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub REST API</a>
        (<code>api.github.com</code>) to display the current star count for the loam.dev repository.
        This call is made by your browser and transmits your IP address to GitHub (GitHub, Inc., a Microsoft subsidiary, San Francisco, CA, USA —
        a third country under GDPR).
        <strong>This call occurs only on the home page.</strong> No other page contacts GitHub.
        The legal basis is Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR — legitimate interest in showing a live community signal.
        Third-country transfer: GitHub processes data in the United States; an adequacy decision exists for EU–US Data Privacy Framework participants.
        GitHub's privacy policy: <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Privacy Statement</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Cookies &amp; Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This website sets <strong>no cookies</strong>, uses <strong>no tracking scripts</strong>,
        and integrates <strong>no analytics or advertising services</strong>.
        No consent banner is needed because there is nothing to consent to.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Under the GDPR you have the right to access, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing,
        data portability, and the right to object. To exercise these rights, contact
        <a href="mailto:silvio-lindstedt@outlook.com">silvio-lindstedt@outlook.com</a>.
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        This policy is versioned in the public repository at
        <a href="https://github.com/silvio-l/loam" rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/silvio-l/loam</a>.
        Material changes will be noted in the repository changelog.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style is:inline>
  /* Privacy-specific overrides: tighter column and spacing for a legal document. */
  .prose-page {
    max-width: 68ch;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }
  .prose-page h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .prose-page h2 {
    margin: 2rem 0 .6rem;
  }
  .prose-page section:first-of-type {
    border-top: none;
  }
</style>
